x=\cos A\cos B,y=\cos A\sin B,z=\sin A
\cos A\cos B+\cos A\sin B+\sin A=\cos A\sqrt2\cos(B-\frac\pi4)+\sin A\le \sqrt2\cos A+\sin A
\sqrt2=R\cos C,1=R\sin C
R>0\implies R^2=2+1=3,R=\sqrt3, \cos C=\sqrt\frac23
\implies \sqrt2\cos A+\sin A=\sqrt3\cos(A-\arccos\sqrt\frac23)\le \sqrt 3
x+y+z\le \sqrt3
A-\arccos\sqrt\frac23=2n\pi\implies \cos A=\sqrt\frac23
